sections.question:
A population of juveniles and adults is modelled by $\mathbf{p}_{n+1}=L\mathbf{p}_n$ with $L= egin{pmatrix}0&1.5\0.6&0.8\end{pmatrix}$. Using your GDC where appropriate: 
 (a) find the eigenvalues of $L$; 
 (b) state the long-term annual percentage growth rate of the population; 
 (c) find the long-term ratio of juveniles to adults. [6]
